    "text": [
        "Dear Sara,",
        "How are you? It\u2019s been a long time since I have spoken to you after graduation. I hope you have adjusted well with your new job and enjoying the new environment. Well, I am writing to check if you still have my book which I gave you last year.",
        "I remember giving the booking in May 2019 during our mid semester break. The book\u2019s title was \u2019The Secret\u2019 and had a yellow cover. I think you finished reading half of the book while we were in contact, just before I left for Auckland for further studies.",
        "Just today, while I was cleaning my book shelve, I realised that I am missing the book. This book is very special to me as it was gifted by my grandmother on my 21st birthday. Sadly, she passed away few months back so I want to treasure all her gifts and belongings that could remind me of her love and affection.",
        "I would be more than happy if you want to return the book in person, it would be a great chance for us to catch up. Let me know what suits you the best.",
        "Warm regards,",
        "Rachana."
